author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | DeSales, Jonathan Alder clinch division titles
text:
DeSales 28, St. Charles 6 Austin Andrews scored on two TD runs, and DeSales (8-1, 2-0) clinched the Central Catholic League Silver division title with win at host St. Charles (3-6, 0-2).
Davion Johnson put the Cardinals ahead early with a 9-yard TD run before Andrews scored his first-half TDs sandwiched around a 51-yard TD pass from Dylan Todd to Ryan Corkrean. | BOX SCORE 
Jonathan Alder 28, River Valley 22 Sean Sullivan rushed for 218 yards on 37 carries and scored two touchdowns to help Jonathan Alder (8-1, 6-0) clinch the Mid-Ohio Athletic Conference Red Division with a win over visiting River Valley (6-3, 4-2).
Sullivan, who has 1,040 rushing yards this season, scored on a 5-yard run to give the Pioneers a 28-14 lead with 4:50 remaining. Jax Harville threw a pair of scoring passes to Carson Parcell for River Valley.  | BOX SCORE 
Worthington Kilbourne 28, New Albany 22 Josh Stoner scored three touchdowns to lead Worthington Kilbourne (8-1, 5-1) over host New Albany (5-4, 4-2).
Stoner returned a punt 55 yards for a touchdown, caught a 55-yard scoring pass and scored the winning touchdown on a 9-yard pass reception. | BOX SCORE 
Olentangy Orange 21, Big Walnut 14 Tyler Lichter scored the go-ahead touchdown on a 1-yard run midway through the fourth quarter to lead Olentangy Orange (3-6, 3-3) over visiting Big Walnut (2-7, 1-5) in the OCC Capital.
Lichter, who finished with 76 yards rushing, also scored on a 6-yard run. Evan Garcia led Big Walnut with 76 rushing yards and a 20-yard TD reception. | BOX SCORE 
Beechcroft 41, Whetstone 12 Macyah Fleming, Rodell Rahmaan and Kyle Barrett each accounted for two touchdowns and Beechcroft (6-2, 5-0), despite getting outgained 250-245 in total yards, downed host Whetstone (4-5, 3-2) in the City North.
Fleming ran for a score and threw a 61 yard TD pass to Rahmann, who also had a punt return for a touchdown. Barrett also threw a touchdown pass and ran one in. Whetstone QB Jack Staggs had 231 yards passing and Aidan Tuttle had 10 receptions for 82 yards. | BOX SCORE 
Fairfield Union 28, Liberty Union 14 Braden Hefton scored on a 32-yard run in the fourth quarter to help Fairfield Union (4-5, 2-4) pull away from visiting Liberty Union (1-8, 0-6) in the MSL Buckeye.
Hefton rushed for 106 yards and two TDs. | BOX SCORE 
Pickerington Central 34, Groveport 10 Seth Currens and Xavier Henderson scored twice, and Pickerington Central (7-2, 5-1) beat host Groveport (5-4, 2-4) to remain tied for the first place in the OCC Ohio.
Currens had a 26-yard TD run and returned a fumble 22 yards for a score. Henderson had a 15-yard TD run and a 90-yard kickoff return for a TD. Devon McMillin added two FGs for the Tigers. | BOX SCORE 
Danville 41, Lucas 0 Ridge Durbin passed for 341 yards and rushed for 141, and Danville (9-0, 2-0) won the showdown between the No. 1 and 2 teams in the Division VII state poll, defeating visiting Lucas (8-1, 1-1) in the Mid-Buckeye Conference.
Durbin threw four touchdown passes and ran for another TD to keep Danville undefeated on the year. | BOX SCORE
